      "content": "To fix the dripping sink, you'll need a small flathead screwdriver, adjustable wrench, adjustable pliers, and replacement washer. Turn off the water supply lines, use the adjustable wrench to remove the old washer, and replace it with the new one. Then, reconnect the supply lines and test the sink. Cleaning the underside of the sink might also be helpful to ensure no debris is obstructing the drain or the washer.",
